<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-266] Produce initial content for the doc/protocol project </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-266</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Contract No. SFS-DEV-005 with Open Scalable File Systems, Inc., calls for a git repository. The contents of the repository is to be &apos;asciidoc&apos; documents that explain the Lustre protocols for Ptlrpc. There will likely be other content as well, including figures drawn in graphviz and perhaps other formats. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This bug is for producing initial content for the new repository, which has already been created (TEI-3041). That (currently empty) repository can be checked out with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  git clone ssh://uselton@review.whamcloud.com:29418/doc/protocol&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A separate ticket (TEI-3065) will add the repository to the &quot;post message to Jira when Gerrit gets a new patch&quot; whitelist.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In addition to new content, I will also need to initialize my local, checked-out repository so that it will &quot;push to review&quot; correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
